{
  "text": "The choice of an access route to WOPN should depend on the extent of necrosis and the experience of a medical center [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Comparing the results of treatment presented in this report with the publication originating from our center concerning 112 patients with WOPN who underwent conventional drainage [CITATION_4] , we conclude that with the increase of experience in the field of drainage procedures there is an improvement in the efficiency and safety of therapy.",
